<h3 class="date"><a href="/2009/jan/06/">&#x27a0;</a> January 6, 2009</h3>


<div class="row">
    <div class="span12">


    
    <div class="well" id="weak-password-brings-happiness" >

        

        <h4><a class="taggedlink linklink" href="http://blog.wired.com/27bstroke6/2009/01/professed-twitt.html">Weak Password Brings &#39;Happiness&#39; to Twitter Hacker</a></h4>

        
            
        

        <p>Full details on yesterday&#8217;s Twitter hack. Twitter&#8217;s admin interface was available offsite to all their admin users, one of whom has a weak password, plus their monitoring didn&#8217;t notice a dictionary attack going on.  Oops.</p>

        <div class="row-fluid">
            <div class="span10">
                
                    Filed under
                    
                        : <a rel="tag" class="tag" href="/tag/security/">security</a>
                    
                        : <a rel="tag" class="tag" href="/tag/twitter/">twitter</a>
                    
                
            </div>
